Expected completion time of project, [latex]\; T_{E\, project}=200\, days[/latex] Standard deviation of project, [latex]\begin{aligned}
 \sigma _{project}&=6.1\, days\\ Z&= \frac{T_{S}-T_{E}}{\sigma _{project}} \\ &=\frac{T_{S}-T_{E\, project}}{\sigma _{project}}\\ 1.64&= \frac{T_{S}-200}{6.1}\\ T_{S}&=200+6.1\times 1.64\\  &=200+10.004\\  &=210.004 \simeq 210\, days
\end{aligned}[/latex]

On stress path in terms of p-q plot [latex]
\begin{aligned}
p=\frac{\sigma_{1}+\sigma_{3}}{2} \\
q=\frac{\sigma_{1}-\sigma_{3}}{2}
\end{aligned}[/latex] If [latex]\sigma_{1}=\sigma_{3}[/latex] then [latex]q=0[/latex] and [latex]p \neq 0[/latex] hence point does 
not lie at origin, point will lies on the p-axis. If [latex]\sigma_{1}>\sigma_{3}[/latex], both the stress point will be positive.
